There's a discussion in a followup about this in @4588, but it wasn't addressed by an instructor. As it seems to stand, if the waitlist begins processing during Phase 2, you will be enrolled ahead of all non-majors, but if the waitlist begins processing during the adjustment period, you will be enrolled in the position you are in, regardless of who is ahead of you.

______

Since the TA hiring hasn't been finalized, CS170 enrollment will be capped at 70% of its capacity. All majored students will get enrolled directly until the 70% is filled up. Me myself is on wl 308, and it's because the 70% enrollment cap is full.

There's a discussion in a followup about this in @4588, but it wasn't addressed by an instructor. As it seems to stand, if the waitlist begins processing during Phase 2, you will be enrolled ahead of all non-majors, but if the waitlist begins processing during the adjustment period, you will be enrolled in the position you are in, regardless of who is ahead of you.

I'm a (declared) EECS major and enrolled in CS 170 during my phase II today. I was put in place 307 on the waitlist. When adjustment period comes around and the remaining 30% of the class is filled, do I have priority because I'm declared? What are my chances of being able to enroll? Thanks.
